(2087, 'EE', '101', 'A', 'Elektrik Elektronik Mühendisliğine Giriş', 'Mühendislik Fakültesi', 2.00, 'GÖKTÜRK POYRAZOĞLU', 'UG Tam', '', '', 'Öğrenciler, EE müfredatındaki dersler ile birlikte meslekleri hakkında genel bir bakış edineceklerdir. Temel EE mühendislik problemlerini analiz edecek ve çözeceklerdir. Konular arasında mühendislik hesaplaması, lineer cebir, olasılık ve istatistik, dijital sistemler, devre analizi, sinyal işleme, iletişim sistemleri, gömülü sistemler, elektromanyetizma, güç sistemleri ve optik yer almaktadır.', 'Pazartesi | 10:40 - 12:30'),
(2088, 'EE', '201', 'A', 'Sinyaller ve Sistemler', 'Mühendislik Fakültesi', 6.00, 'EVŞEN YANMAZ ADAM', 'UG Tam', 'MATH 212', '', 'Topics include basic continuous and discrete time signals and systems, linear time invariant systems, Fourier analysis for continuous and discrete time signals and systems, filtering and modulation, sampling and aliasing, and Laplace and z-transform.', 'Perşembe | 11:40 - 14:30'),
(2089, 'EE', '202', 'A', 'Devre Analizi', 'Mühendislik Fakültesi', 6.00, 'UMUT BAŞARAN', 'UG Tam', 'EE 202L', 'MATH 211 and PHYS102', 'Basic circuit concepts (Voltage, Current, Node, Mesh, Measurement Units), Basic circuit analysis methods (Node voltage analysis, Mesh current analysis), Circuit elements, Active sources and active circuits, operational amplifiers, time varying signals, capacitors, inductors, first and second order circuits, circuit analysis using Laplace transform.', 'Salı | 08:40 - 10:30Çarşamba | 08:40 - 10:30'),
(2090, 'EE', '202L', 'A', 'Devre Analizi - Lab.', 'Mühendislik Fakültesi', 0.00, 'UMUT BAŞARAN', 'UG Tam', 'EE 202', '', '', 'Cuma | 14:40 - 17:30'),
(2091, 'EE', '203', 'A', 'Sayısal Sistemler', 'Mühendislik Fakültesi', 6.00, 'İLKER HAMZAOĞLU', 'UG Tam', 'EE 203L', '', 'This course teaches the basics of digital logic design but yet emphasizes high-level aspects of digital systems design -- as the word systems in the course name implies. In that context, it is critical to understand analog versus digital, sensors, system I/O, waveforms, timing, area, power, and cost issues. As modern digital design problems are large, they can only be addressed with a scalable hence language based approach. In this course, we write digital designs in Verilog language (similar to C) for the most part and map them to FPGAs. In the lab, we also implement digital circuits with discrete components – the traditional way, in addition to Verilog on FPGAs.', 'Salı | 11:40 - 14:30'),
