(2842, 'ARCH', '212', 'A', 'Çevre Analizi ve Sürdürülebilir Peyzaj Tasarımı', 'Mimarlık ve Tasarım Fakültesi', 3.00, 'DOĞA DİNEMİS AMAN', 'UG Tam', '', '', 'This course aims to develop the understanding and skills of site analysis and landscape design through elaborating different layers of landscape in the context of sustainability. The recent concepts and theories of landscape, ecological systems and sustainability issues will be introduced in order to contextualize the issues. Site analysis will include comprehension of climate, topography, geology, hydrology, flora and flora, fabric and typologies of open spaces, cultural and architectural layers, and how all are interacting with each other. The course will be focused on landscape planning and design, particularly on the development of design concept and process of design in landscape, forms, functions, grading, water management, planting and habitat construction, structures, furniture and materials with the perspective of ecological systems thinking. Besides, presentation techniques in landscape architecture will be integrated to the process.', 'Cuma | 08:40 - 11:30'),
